                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/707.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-07T19:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">June</hi> 7, 1912—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Speaker of the House of Representatives, Ferrara, left today on unannounced
                    trip to Washington. I am reliably informed he is special representative of
                    President Gómez to ask further aid in protecting property, but more particularly
                    to plead for time to crush rebellion. This information is from private
                    sources.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
